<br>
Another options, that might be logistically friendly, but with less risk (and subsequently maybe less fun):<br>
<br>
Highkeep Basement - Don't know if it gets much play these days, back before Kunark you had to wait on lists for hours to get a group down here.  The dungeon is the size of a large Inn, you can melee bind there, and the bank is up two flights of stairs from the monsters, whom you can train to Guards if you get in over your head.<br>
<br>
Its good for 20s to 35.<br>
<br>
Not the most exciting EQ experience, but its a convenient place for pickup grouping. Try convincing pickup strangers to go to ToFS... :-p <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucoslinroguebarbarian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CoslinRogueBarbarian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/25/02 7:52:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2792.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well...</span><hr size=1> Highkeep is the 1 place I want to stay FAR FAR away from. Simple reason being the same theory as Paludal: Nonsense from people just trying to Powerlevel. The crying and complaining is almost ear-shattering. <br>
