<br>
I'm thinking at level 30 I'd like to be trying my hand at the Mines of Nurga, Temple of Droga (grouped), Crystal Caverns (again, done it with a SK and Enc), or maybe Mistmoore (a zone I've never really done much in).  As a solo rogue, you could sneak through some of the hard parts and get a feel for the place.  I don't know if sneaking through risky areas is enough to quicken the pace of your blood but I doubt any of those areas would see you.  Your Safe Fall skill could be a minor boon in some of those areas.  Sneak certainly would.  I don't know how you'll manage splitting mobs while solo though, so you may end up soloing near zone lines.  I don't want to spoil any of those zones for you if you haven't been there yet but you may have to do a bit of sneaking to get to a relatively safe spot.<br>
<br>
My beastlord is currently only 25th level and will probably be harassing the critters near ill omen for a while.<br>
