<br>
Have you tried Dawnshroud Peaks?  As long as you can avoid the wolves (learn where they are and don't go there), most things are not social or agressive.  The Zelniak's are great for skill training (and experience), the mushrooms are good for money as well, plus there are several wandering tribals which would be single pulls.<br>
<br>
About duos... they can be a lot more dynamic than a full group and then you have someone with whom to chat in your down time.  As much as I like full groups for the stuff we can take down, I almost prefer a duo.  I -love- wandering and don't really like &quot;camping&quot; one spot.  As a ranger, I -can- solo, but I will generally take up a duo in a heart beat (there are moments when I want to solo, but not always for the skill or loot or other such reasons.. there are times I jsut want solitude).<br>
<br>
